There is no evidence that dietary protein increases the risk of hip fracture. 2. There is no evidence that dietary protein decreases calcium excretion. 3. There is no evidence that dietary protein stimulates production of growth hormone. 4. There is no evidence that dietary protein reduces muscle mass and strength.

Does dietary protein affect hip fractures? There is no definitive answer to this question. Some studies suggest that a high protein diet may increase the risk of hip fractures, while other studies suggest that a high protein diet may help protect against hip fractures. More research is needed to determine the relationship between dietary protein and hip fractures.
Does dietary protein affect calcium excretion? There is no clear evidence that dietary protein affects calcium excretion.
Does dietary protein affect production of growth hormone? There is no evidence that dietary protein affects production of growth hormone.

What does additional dietary increase, decrease, or stimulate? An increase in dietary intake would generally mean that the person is eating more food. A decrease in dietary intake would generally mean that the person is eating less food. Stimulation of dietary intake would generally mean that the person is eating more food and experiencing a sense of hunger.
What increases risk of hip fracture? Aging, low bone density, and weak muscles are the main risk factors for hip fracture.
What decreases calcium excretion? A decrease in calcium excretion can be caused by a low intake of calcium, a high intake of phosphorus, or a high intake of vitamin D.

What stimulates production of insulin-like growth hormone? The most common stimulus for the production of insulin-like growth hormone is the presence of growth hormone-releasing hormone (GHRH) in the hypothalamus.
What is the basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue? The basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue is the muscle fiber.
What is the most common naturally-occurring form in which silicon is found? Silicon is most commonly found in the form of silica, or silicon dioxide.

Is silicon dioxide the same as oxide? No, silicon dioxide is not the same as oxide. Silicon dioxide is a compound made up of two elements, silicon and oxygen. Oxide is an element made up of oxygen and another element.
Is silicon found in sulfide? No, silicon is not found in sulfide. Silicon is a chemical element with the symbol Si and atomic number 14. Sulfide is a chemical compound with the formula S2.
Is silicon found in fluoride? No, silicon is not found in fluoride.
Is silicon found in metallic element? No, silicon is not found in metallic elements. Silicon is a semiconductor.

What did the Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions do? The treaty, which was signed by the United States and Russia in 2002, committed both countries to reduce their stockpiles of nuclear weapons.
In 2017, what was the percentage of the Saudi Arabia GDP spent on military? In 2017, the percentage of the Saudi Arabia GDP spent on military was 10.7%.
